[right top of page]          5-6-83   Smither     350
since writing the above I think some cows with calves could be purchased with Calves 3 or 4 months old for from $20 to $24 dollars and perhaps much less.  I mention these figures for if you pay Mrs Brennan 15.50 you would be paying her $33 for cow and calf, and I am told that calves could be purchased at much less, from $5 to $6. each.  I will  make further inquiries about this and write you.   This is stated from talk with the butcher here, and I can not say that I will depend on him, but would like to know your figures, as follows so as to guide me, the amount you will pay
for Cows, without calf,
for Cows with calf,
for Steers, over 2 years,
for Steers under 2 years,
for Calves one year
for Calves under one year.
Smither
Captain
